CHUAH CHOO CHIANG:   Nicholas, views of your match against Graeme and Jamie?   You were up for a long time but team Europe came back to win.   Your thoughts, please?   
NICHOLAS FUNG:   We played solid the first six holes.   We was 2‑up until the eighth hole, and missed a short putt on 9.   11, they make a quite long birdie putt to halve the hole.   But 13, 15, 16, I missed a short putt and that's why we lost.   
   
 Q.   When you started today, you had to have some treatment on the putting green from the physio.   Is there any repercussions from that in today's round and will it affect you tomorrow?   
NICHOLAS FUNG:   No, just a little swollen in the wrist when hitting the ball on the range.   But before I'm going out, it was fine, really fine.   
   
